beer_brewer_name: Wild Goose Brewery (Frederick Brewing Company/Flying Dog)
review_blob: Warm overtones. Nutty malty flavor. Not strong alcohol wise. Smooth for a winter ale
A delicous strong hoppy taste. The blend of hops is expert ~ most "hopped" dont have the delicate aftertaste and the wonderful finish. Highly reccomended
Fresh tasting for an pastuerized mport goes down smoothly and leaves an overall good im pression
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Pure Brewed Organic Lager

review_blob: Interesting. Everyone says sweet, but my bottle is sour. I do taste the bananna. I like the strong flavor.
Hoppy and malty with strong alcohol taste. Definately has a chocolate taste. Needs more refinement
i darnk it warm - fruity taste, goes down smooth quite drinkable. Cant taste the alcohol bit its there
The fruity taste Juniper? I thought cardoman. A different taste unpastuerized and fresh. Good though I wouldnt drink it on a regualr basis.
Very big head at pour, lots of spice hints -nutmeg? cinnamion? a really oriiginal well spiced beed
Delicious very thick, potent, small head, goes down fast though not as alcohol tasting as one might expect
Delicious, strong not a big head, hoppy definaelty gets one drunk, one bottle is all you need not as good as the cask 120 I had
This is a delicious ale. My bottle 75cl, 9.4% alc. Drinking it warm on christmas eve, it goes down big with a hint of spice at the back of the tongue.
